CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 1, 1941, pg. 2, reads: "McEvoy Remodels Store - To our many customers who have made this improvement possible. We extend sincere thanks: we will try to serve you just as efficient in future as we have in the past.  Insert show C. McEvoy, owner of this up-to-date store.  Agents for the famous BULOVA watches and RCA radios.  Mr. McEvoy is not only a Jeweler, but a Watchmaker and Engraver located at 1411 WYLIE AVENUE."
TitMainTitle: Storefront of C. McEvoy Jeweler, 1411 Wylie Avenue, Hill District
